"{\"abstract\":\"We present a global and convex formulation for template-less 3D reconstruction of a deforming object with the perspective camera. We show for the first time how to construct a Second-Order Cone Programming (SOCP) problem for Non-Rigid Shape-from-Motion (NRSfM) using the Maximum-Depth Heuristic (MDH). In this regard, we deviate strongly from the general trend of using affine cameras and factorization-based methods to solve NRSfM. In MDH, the points' depths are maximized so that the distance between neighbouring points in camera space are upper bounded by the geodesic distance. In NRSfM both geodesic and camera space distances are unknown. We show that, nonetheless, given point correspondences and the camera's intrinsics the whole problem is convex and solvable with SOCP. We show with extensive experiments that our method accurately reconstructs quasi-isometric surfaces from partial views under articulated and strong deformations. It naturally handles missing correspondences, non-smooth objects and is very simple to implement compared to previous methods, with only one free parameter (the neighbourhood size).\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2572459\",\"name\":\"Ajad Chhatkuli\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2572459\"},{\"authorId\":\"1403319406\",\"name\":\"Daniel Pizarro-Perez\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1403319406\"},{\"authorId\":\"2161419\",\"name\":\"T. Collins\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2161419\"},{\"authorId\":\"153281218\",\"name\":\"A. Bartoli\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/153281218\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"1902.10840\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"49580981\",\"name\":\"Chen Kong\"},{\"authorId\":\"1820249\",\"name\":\"S. Lucey\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"be1b9a81ec07494b38e80954a3ebf18e7cd1ac3f\",\"title\":\"Deep Interpretable Non-Rigid Structure from Motion\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/be1b9a81ec07494b38e80954a3ebf18e7cd1ac3f\",\"venue\":\"ArXiv\",\"year\":2019},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3460588\",\"name\":\"Geonho Cha\"},{\"authorId\":\"2646766\",\"name\":\"Minsik Lee\"},{\"authorId\":\"2803030\",\"name\":\"Jungchan Cho\"},{\"authorId\":\"34184385\",\"name\":\"Songhwai Oh\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1016/j.patrec.2018.03.019\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"5e504b415ac1577954d5efd8bb0c72d82196d6ac\",\"title\":\"Non-rigid surface recovery with a robust local-rigidity prior\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/5e504b415ac1577954d5efd8bb0c72d82196d6ac\",\"venue\":\"Pattern Recognit. Lett.\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3380804\",\"name\":\"Shaifali Parashar\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"e723e4c4ae2d77c8efab6a7cf1b13e7ea7ae5c1b\",\"title\":\"Image-based Deformable 3D Reconstruction using Differential Geometry and Cartan's Connections. (Reconstruction 3D d\\u00e9formable bas\\u00e9e sur l'image utilisant la g\\u00e9om\\u00e9trie diff\\u00e9rentielle et les connexions de Cartan)\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/e723e4c4ae2d77c8efab6a7cf1b13e7ea7ae5c1b\",\"venue\":\"\",\"year\":2017},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3380804\",\"name\":\"Shaifali Parashar\"},{\"authorId\":\"153281218\",\"name\":\"A. Bartoli\"},{\"authorId\":\"1403319406\",\"name\":\"Daniel Pizarro-Perez\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/978-3-030-01246-5_16\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"7d11a9e342d6639431e3751fb01a6223494a6941\",\"title\":\"Self-Calibrating Isometric Non-Rigid Structure-from-Motion\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/7d11a9e342d6639431e3751fb01a6223494a6941\",\"venue\":\"ECCV\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"35030887\",\"name\":\"Mathias Gallardo\"},{\"authorId\":\"2161419\",\"name\":\"T. Collins\"},{\"